WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.556 --> 00:00:04.518
[ominous music]

2
00:00:04.601 --> 00:00:11.483
<i>♪♪</i>

3
00:00:33.046 --> 00:00:35.966
[engine rumbling]

4
00:00:36.049 --> 00:00:42.973
<i>♪♪</i>

5
00:00:44.391 --> 00:00:46.434
<i>♪ Who's sorry now? ♪</i>

6
00:00:46.518 --> 00:00:48.228
[sipping]

7
00:00:48.311 --> 00:00:50.438
[soft country music playing on speakers]

8
00:00:50.522 --> 00:00:51.731
Can I get another one of these?

9
00:00:51.815 --> 00:00:53.692
No.

10
00:00:53.775 --> 00:00:55.777
Fine.

11
00:00:55.861 --> 00:01:00.615
<i>♪ Whose heart is achin' for breakin' ♪</i>

12
00:01:00.699 --> 00:01:02.158
What. did you think
we'd find him in a day?

13
00:01:02.242 --> 00:01:03.869
It's been three. Billie.

14
00:01:03.952 --> 00:01:05.370
[door bell jingles]

15
00:01:05.453 --> 00:01:07.038
- I'm tired.
- I need to find him.

16
00:01:07.122 --> 00:01:08.498
I don't know where else to look.

17
00:01:08.582 --> 00:01:11.001
God damn it. Billie!
I need to find him.

18
00:01:11.084 --> 00:01:13.211
[foreboding music]

19
00:01:13.295 --> 00:01:15.171
[distant dog barking]

20
00:01:18.008 --> 00:01:22.095
[door bell jingling]

21
00:01:22.178 --> 00:01:25.140
[indistinct conversation]

22
00:01:25.223 --> 00:01:32.147
<i>♪♪</i>

23
00:02:04.137 --> 00:02:05.597
[door bell jingling]

24
00:02:09.142 --> 00:02:10.727
Hello. Albert.

25
00:02:10.810 --> 00:02:12.187
What are you doing here?

26
00:02:12.270 --> 00:02:14.689
Please come with me. Now.

27
00:02:14.773 --> 00:02:17.943
[muffled speech]

28
00:02:18.026 --> 00:02:20.445
That is not your milkshake. Albert.

29
00:02:20.528 --> 00:02:22.238
Come on.
[gunshots]

30
00:02:22.322 --> 00:02:25.325
[clattering]

31
00:02:25.408 --> 00:02:28.328
[gunshots]

32
00:02:32.415 --> 00:02:33.833
[person screams]

33
00:02:33.917 --> 00:02:40.382
<i>♪♪</i>

34
00:02:43.301 --> 00:02:44.260
[gunshot]

35
00:02:44.344 --> 00:02:47.263
[panting]

36
00:02:49.766 --> 00:02:52.686
[gunshots]

37
00:02:52.769 --> 00:02:54.479
[moaning]

38
00:02:56.064 --> 00:02:58.233
[panting]

39
00:03:00.235 --> 00:03:02.237
[gunshots. glass shattering]

40
00:03:04.823 --> 00:03:06.408
[engine humming]

41
00:03:06.491 --> 00:03:09.035
Go. go. go! Go!

42
00:03:09.119 --> 00:03:16.042
<i>♪♪</i>

43
00:03:20.255 --> 00:03:23.550
[moody guitar music]

44
00:03:23.633 --> 00:03:30.557
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

45
00:04:08.762 --> 00:04:11.598
{\an8}[Bad Company's "Seagull"]

46
00:04:11.681 --> 00:04:13.349
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

47
00:04:13.433 --> 00:04:14.851
{\an8}[vocalizing]

48
00:04:14.934 --> 00:04:16.436
{\an8}[horse snorts]

49
00:04:16.519 --> 00:04:23.401
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

50
00:04:27.739 --> 00:04:29.866
{\an8}<i>♪ Seagull. you fly ♪</i>

51
00:04:29.949 --> 00:04:32.494
{\an8}<i>♪ Across the horizon ♪</i>

52
00:04:32.577 --> 00:04:36.998
{\an8}<i>♪ Into the misty morning sun ♪</i>

53
00:04:37.082 --> 00:04:41.002
{\an8}[grunting]

54
00:04:41.086 --> 00:04:46.674
{\an8}<i>♪ Nobody asked you</i>
<i>where you are going ♪</i>

55
00:04:46.758 --> 00:04:50.970
{\an8}<i>♪ Nobody knows</i>
<i>where you're from ♪</i>

56
00:04:51.054 --> 00:04:53.890
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

57
00:04:53.973 --> 00:04:56.351
{\an8}<i>♪ Here is a man ♪</i>

58
00:04:56.434 --> 00:04:59.020
{\an8}<i>♪ Asking the question ♪</i>

59
00:04:59.104 --> 00:05:03.733
{\an8}<i>♪ Is this really</i>
<i>the end of the world? ♪</i>

60
00:05:03.817 --> 00:05:05.026
{\an8}[horse snorts]

61
00:05:07.070 --> 00:05:12.492
{\an8}<i>♪ Seagull. you must have known</i>
<i>for a long time ♪</i>

62
00:05:12.575 --> 00:05:16.871
{\an8}<i>♪ The shape of things to come ♪</i>

63
00:05:16.955 --> 00:05:22.335
{\an8}<i>♪ Now you fly through the sky ♪</i>

64
00:05:22.418 --> 00:05:26.339
{\an8}<i>♪ Never asking why ♪</i>

65
00:05:26.422 --> 00:05:31.469
{\an8}<i>♪ And you fly all around ♪</i>

66
00:05:31.553 --> 00:05:35.306
{\an8}<i>♪ Till somebody ♪</i>

67
00:05:35.390 --> 00:05:39.352
{\an8}<i>♪ Shoots you down ♪</i>

68
00:05:39.435 --> 00:05:42.063
{\an8}<i>♪ Da. da. da. da. da down ♪</i>

69
00:05:42.146 --> 00:05:43.398
{\an8}[wind howling]

70
00:05:43.481 --> 00:05:46.693
{\an8}[vocalizing]

71
00:05:46.776 --> 00:05:53.700
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

72
00:05:53.783 --> 00:05:55.493
{\an8}[speaking Diné]

73
00:05:55.577 --> 00:05:57.328
{\an8}<i>♪ Seagull. you fly ♪</i>

74
00:05:57.412 --> 00:05:59.664
{\an8}[gunshot]

75
00:05:59.747 --> 00:06:04.127
{\an8}<i>♪ And you fly away today ♪</i>

76
00:06:04.210 --> 00:06:07.881
{\an8}<i>♪ And you fly away tomorrow ♪</i>

77
00:06:07.964 --> 00:06:09.340
{\an8}[horse snorts]

78
00:06:09.424 --> 00:06:14.053
{\an8}<i>♪ Seagull. go and fly ♪</i>

79
00:06:14.137 --> 00:06:18.808
{\an8}[vocalizing]

80
00:06:18.892 --> 00:06:23.438
{\an8}<i>♪ Fly to your tomorrow ♪</i>

81
00:06:23.521 --> 00:06:28.234
{\an8}<i>♪ Lead me to my sorrow ♪</i>

82
00:06:28.318 --> 00:06:31.613
{\an8}<i>♪ Fly ♪</i>

83
00:06:31.696 --> 00:06:38.620
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

84
00:07:07.398 --> 00:07:10.610
[soft music]

85
00:07:10.693 --> 00:07:17.200
<i>♪♪</i>

86
00:07:19.285 --> 00:07:22.413
Horses are fed.

87
00:07:22.497 --> 00:07:24.916
I filled the water tank.

88
00:07:24.999 --> 00:07:26.668
switched out those two batteries.

89
00:07:26.751 --> 00:07:28.211
It's gonna be a hot one today.

90
00:07:28.294 --> 00:07:30.088
And you also cook. apparently.

91
00:07:30.171 --> 00:07:31.589
Yeah.

92
00:07:31.673 --> 00:07:34.592
There's so much
you don't know about me.

93
00:07:34.676 --> 00:07:36.803
Oh. yeah? Like what?

94
00:07:36.886 --> 00:07:39.264
I've also been known to embellish.

95
00:07:39.347 --> 00:07:40.682
Oh.

96
00:07:40.765 --> 00:07:43.601
You got the big words going on too.

97
00:07:43.685 --> 00:07:45.353
Mm.

98
00:07:45.436 --> 00:07:46.521
College.

99
00:07:46.604 --> 00:07:47.730
It's not for everyone.

100
00:07:47.814 --> 00:07:49.482
[giggles] Whatever.

101
00:07:49.565 --> 00:07:50.858
Mm.

102
00:07:50.942 --> 00:07:52.819
Go to work.

103
00:07:52.902 --> 00:07:54.821
All right then.

104
00:07:54.904 --> 00:07:55.989
See you tonight.

105
00:07:56.072 --> 00:07:57.532
Mm-hmm.

106
00:07:57.615 --> 00:07:59.993
[sighs] You sure
you don't wanna come?

107
00:08:00.076 --> 00:08:01.828
It'd make Felix's day.

108
00:08:01.911 --> 00:08:05.123
[sighs] So now
Felix is the carrot?

109
00:08:05.206 --> 00:08:07.166
Well. it's either him or Bigman.

110
00:08:07.250 --> 00:08:08.459
[chuckles]

111
00:08:09.544 --> 00:08:12.213
I'll let you know if anything changes.

112
00:08:12.297 --> 00:08:13.798
How about that?

113
00:08:13.881 --> 00:08:15.675
You know you can't just feed horses

114
00:08:15.758 --> 00:08:17.719
for the rest of your life. can you?

115
00:08:17.802 --> 00:08:19.637
No.

116
00:08:19.721 --> 00:08:22.140
That's what I keep you around for.

117
00:08:22.223 --> 00:08:24.726
- Well. if that's
the price of admission.

118
00:08:24.809 --> 00:08:26.728
I'll start pulling extra shifts.

119
00:08:29.063 --> 00:08:30.898
[speaking Diné]

120
00:08:30.982 --> 00:08:32.900
[speaking Diné]

121
00:08:37.572 --> 00:08:38.489
[sighs]

122
00:08:43.369 --> 00:08:46.372
[engine humming]

123
00:08:54.213 --> 00:08:55.715
[engine stops]

124
00:08:57.967 --> 00:09:00.428
Hey. now.

125
00:09:00.511 --> 00:09:01.929
Gordo.

126
00:09:02.013 --> 00:09:03.765
Looks like you
could use some help.

127
00:09:03.848 --> 00:09:05.683
I wouldn't say no.

128
00:09:11.939 --> 00:09:14.942
Goddamn neighbor of mine's
building a garage.

129
00:09:15.026 --> 00:09:16.652
Every nail he pounds into the frame.

130
00:09:16.736 --> 00:09:20.114
he drops two on my driveway.

131
00:09:20.198 --> 00:09:22.617
Plus. this damn thing's about shot

132
00:09:22.700 --> 00:09:25.453
from stripping these lug nuts.

133
00:09:25.536 --> 00:09:27.121
Where are you headed?

134
00:09:27.205 --> 00:09:32.085
Cabin down near Prescott.
right by the reservoir.

135
00:09:32.168 --> 00:09:34.712
She likes to be out on the water.

136
00:09:34.796 --> 00:09:37.048
Calms her chi. the doctor says.

137
00:09:37.131 --> 00:09:38.549
- Come say hello?
- Yeah.

138
00:09:38.633 --> 00:09:40.093
Yeah.

139
00:09:42.011 --> 00:09:43.721
Oh. well.

140
00:09:43.805 --> 00:09:46.808
Looks like we got some company. B.

141
00:09:46.891 --> 00:09:48.601
Well. hello.

142
00:09:48.684 --> 00:09:50.770
It's been a while.

143
00:09:50.853 --> 00:09:52.855
Yes. ma'am. it has.

144
00:09:52.939 --> 00:09:56.109
You look-- remind me
of your name again.

145
00:09:56.192 --> 00:09:58.736
This is Joe Leaphorn. honey.

146
00:09:58.820 --> 00:10:00.780
Joe. Joe.

147
00:10:00.863 --> 00:10:02.490
Of course.

148
00:10:02.573 --> 00:10:05.743
The last time I saw you.
it was at the church--

149
00:10:05.827 --> 00:10:07.078
the rug auction.

150
00:10:07.161 --> 00:10:08.830
You and Joyce came.

151
00:10:08.913 --> 00:10:12.750
That must have been. like.
what. five years ago?

152
00:10:12.834 --> 00:10:14.961
Yeah. yeah. That's right.

153
00:10:15.044 --> 00:10:16.754
That's Henry you're thinking of.

154
00:10:16.838 --> 00:10:19.632
This is Joe. Henry's son.

155
00:10:19.715 --> 00:10:23.553
You saw him last year
when I was in the hospital.

156
00:10:23.636 --> 00:10:25.471
when David came home.

157
00:10:27.932 --> 00:10:30.309
Yeah. our son. David.

158
00:10:32.103 --> 00:10:33.396
Ah.

159
00:10:33.479 --> 00:10:35.064
As if I could ever forget our son.

160
00:10:35.148 --> 00:10:36.983
You are being so silly.

161
00:10:37.066 --> 00:10:39.235
[chuckling] Oh. no. I can't help it.

162
00:10:41.237 --> 00:10:42.864
Joe.

163
00:10:42.947 --> 00:10:44.198
It's good to see you. ma'am.

164
00:10:44.282 --> 00:10:45.241
[pensive music]

165
00:10:45.324 --> 00:10:48.244
[grunting]

166
00:10:52.331 --> 00:10:53.541
I'm sorry. Gordo.

167
00:10:53.624 --> 00:10:55.460
Yeah.

168
00:10:55.543 --> 00:11:00.673
When our boys left. it's almost
like we were teenagers again.

169
00:11:00.756 --> 00:11:03.634
And I was really looking forward to…

170
00:11:03.718 --> 00:11:05.636
[sighs]

171
00:11:05.720 --> 00:11:08.764
What we'd been robbed of.

172
00:11:08.848 --> 00:11:12.268
When I was in college.
I had this old jalopy.

173
00:11:12.351 --> 00:11:14.187
Rear tire kept losing air.

174
00:11:14.270 --> 00:11:16.898
Not a puncture. just a slow leak.

175
00:11:16.981 --> 00:11:21.068
Every couple days.
I'd have to top it off.

176
00:11:21.152 --> 00:11:25.114
One day. I moved into a house
a block from the school.

177
00:11:25.198 --> 00:11:27.950
Well. didn't need that car anymore.

178
00:11:28.034 --> 00:11:33.289
Next morning. I'd go out.
tire's as flat as a pancake.

179
00:11:33.372 --> 00:11:36.709
[grunts]
First day I didn't need it.

180
00:11:36.792 --> 00:11:39.337
damn thing just gave up.

181
00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:42.173
[sighs]

182
00:11:42.256 --> 00:11:45.009
She needs you
not to give up. Gordo.

183
00:11:45.092 --> 00:11:47.762
whatever that looks like
here on out.

184
00:11:47.845 --> 00:11:51.724
<i>♪♪</i>

185
00:11:51.807 --> 00:11:53.184
[sniffs]

186
00:11:57.772 --> 00:12:00.900
Yeah. you-- you've been doing some

187
00:12:00.983 --> 00:12:03.194
deep thinking since I saw you.

188
00:12:03.277 --> 00:12:06.322
Nothing holds air forever.

189
00:12:06.405 --> 00:12:08.115
That's what I've been thinking.

190
00:12:08.199 --> 00:12:14.288
<i>♪♪</i>

191
00:12:14.372 --> 00:12:15.998
[door bell jingles. door opens]

192
00:12:16.082 --> 00:12:20.461
<i>♪ Reservation radio</i>
<i>listener you love ♪</i>

193
00:12:20.544 --> 00:12:24.006
<i>♪ Handsome old man walking</i>
<i>nine miles to town ♪</i>

194
00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:25.216
Can I help you?

195
00:12:25.299 --> 00:12:26.634
Do you have any maps?

196
00:12:26.717 --> 00:12:27.802
Maps?

197
00:12:27.885 --> 00:12:29.011
Uh. what kind of maps?

198
00:12:29.095 --> 00:12:30.680
I don't know-- road maps?

199
00:12:30.763 --> 00:12:32.265
[sighs. clears throat]

200
00:12:34.058 --> 00:12:35.309
Will this do?

201
00:12:35.393 --> 00:12:37.103
I guess so.

202
00:12:37.186 --> 00:12:39.021
Do you have any gum?

203
00:12:39.105 --> 00:12:42.024
Yeah. I've got Jungle Burst there.
spearmint bubble gum.

204
00:12:42.108 --> 00:12:44.318
- Spearmint.
- All right.

205
00:12:44.402 --> 00:12:45.820
That'll be a buck.

206
00:12:45.903 --> 00:12:46.821
Well. thank you.

207
00:12:46.904 --> 00:12:49.323
Thank you.

208
00:12:49.407 --> 00:12:50.825
[tense music]

209
00:12:50.908 --> 00:12:52.368
[sighs]

210
00:12:52.451 --> 00:12:59.000
<i>♪♪</i>

211
00:12:59.083 --> 00:13:00.626
The frick is this?

212
00:13:00.710 --> 00:13:04.046
<i>♪♪</i>

213
00:13:04.130 --> 00:13:07.300
[muffled shouting]

214
00:13:07.383 --> 00:13:14.265
<i>♪♪</i>

215
00:13:14.348 --> 00:13:16.267
[engine grinds. turns over]

216
00:13:17.768 --> 00:13:20.730
[engine revving]

217
00:13:20.813 --> 00:13:27.486
<i>♪♪</i>

218
00:13:28.529 --> 00:13:31.198
[vehicle approaching]

219
00:13:33.701 --> 00:13:35.077
[engine stops. car door opens]

220
00:13:35.161 --> 00:13:36.579
[horse neighs]

221
00:13:41.751 --> 00:13:43.044
[car door slams]

222
00:13:43.127 --> 00:13:44.045
Joe. that you?

223
00:13:44.128 --> 00:13:45.212
<i>Yeah.</i>

224
00:13:45.296 --> 00:13:46.922
Can you hand me that oil pan?

225
00:13:54.972 --> 00:13:58.059
I brought you some meat.

226
00:13:58.142 --> 00:14:00.728
Thanks.

227
00:14:00.811 --> 00:14:03.689
[horse whinnying]

228
00:14:08.778 --> 00:14:11.447
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing. though.

229
00:14:11.530 --> 00:14:13.741
What. I can't be happy
that you're back?

230
00:14:13.824 --> 00:14:17.912
[chuckles] You won't be happy
until I'm back in uniform.

231
00:14:17.995 --> 00:14:20.581
That's what this is about.

232
00:14:20.665 --> 00:14:25.252
You got Chee working on me.
and now you too.

233
00:14:25.336 --> 00:14:26.545
[sighs]

234
00:14:31.008 --> 00:14:32.301
What is it?

235
00:14:34.553 --> 00:14:37.098
I'm retiring. Bern.

236
00:14:37.181 --> 00:14:38.683
Right.

237
00:14:38.766 --> 00:14:40.184
That's not the first time I've heard that.

238
00:14:40.267 --> 00:14:41.936
No. it's real this time.

239
00:14:42.019 --> 00:14:43.270
Paperwork's in.

240
00:14:43.354 --> 00:14:45.147
Captain Largo's aware.

241
00:14:45.231 --> 00:14:48.609
Come fall. I'm gone.

242
00:14:49.944 --> 00:14:51.028
To where?

243
00:14:54.031 --> 00:14:55.491
Los Angeles?

244
00:14:58.869 --> 00:14:59.787
[sighs]

245
00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:07.753
You know. Emma left
for a reason. Joe.

246
00:15:07.837 --> 00:15:09.338
I'm not sure you trying
to move out there

247
00:15:09.422 --> 00:15:11.215
is gonna make her
change her mind.

248
00:15:11.298 --> 00:15:12.967
She left because she didn't
wanna be with the guy

249
00:15:13.050 --> 00:15:15.344
I was anymore. Bern.

250
00:15:15.428 --> 00:15:17.638
I don't either.

251
00:15:17.722 --> 00:15:19.181
Joe.

252
00:15:19.265 --> 00:15:22.685
Listen. it's just--
it's time for a change.

253
00:15:22.768 --> 00:15:26.647
New blood. new ways of doing
things. new leadership.

254
00:15:26.731 --> 00:15:29.608
[pensive music]

255
00:15:29.692 --> 00:15:30.651
Who?

256
00:15:36.866 --> 00:15:37.825
No!

257
00:15:39.201 --> 00:15:40.161
What?

258
00:15:40.244 --> 00:15:43.164
Uh-- [sighs]

259
00:15:43.247 --> 00:15:44.457
No.

260
00:15:44.540 --> 00:15:46.208
Just think about it.

261
00:15:46.292 --> 00:15:48.085
I don't have to think about it.

262
00:15:48.169 --> 00:15:49.378
I mean. Chee's been here.

263
00:15:49.462 --> 00:15:51.338
I left. and I'm not--

264
00:15:51.422 --> 00:15:52.465
I'm not sure tapping me for the--

265
00:15:52.548 --> 00:15:55.134
I am not saying he is incapable.

266
00:15:55.217 --> 00:15:57.386
He's a good cop. well-trained.

267
00:15:57.470 --> 00:15:59.555
He's serious.

268
00:15:59.638 --> 00:16:02.057
I've come to realize you
cannot separate spirituality

269
00:16:02.141 --> 00:16:05.352
from upholding the law here.

270
00:16:05.436 --> 00:16:09.648
You understand the land.
the people who live on it.

271
00:16:09.732 --> 00:16:11.609
He's still working on that part. Bern.

272
00:16:11.692 --> 00:16:12.860
Yeah.

273
00:16:12.943 --> 00:16:14.320
I--

274
00:16:14.403 --> 00:16:18.032
<i>♪♪</i>

275
00:16:18.115 --> 00:16:20.075
I don't-- I don't know. Joe.

276
00:16:20.159 --> 00:16:22.203
[sighs] Really?

277
00:16:22.286 --> 00:16:23.454
Yeah.

278
00:16:23.537 --> 00:16:25.039
You're the right choice.

279
00:16:25.122 --> 00:16:32.046
<i>♪♪</i>

280
00:16:33.964 --> 00:16:34.965
[sighs]

281
00:16:38.385 --> 00:16:40.387
If you don't know why now…

282
00:16:42.640 --> 00:16:44.225
You will.

283
00:16:49.313 --> 00:16:51.190
[engine turns over]

284
00:16:51.273 --> 00:16:56.695
<i>♪♪</i>

285
00:16:56.779 --> 00:16:58.739
[horse whinnying]

286
00:17:04.036 --> 00:17:06.956
[light music]

287
00:17:07.039 --> 00:17:10.125
<i>♪♪</i>

288
00:17:10.209 --> 00:17:12.670
[phone ringing]

289
00:17:12.753 --> 00:17:15.005
This is going in effect today?

290
00:17:15.089 --> 00:17:17.466
I have dinner plans with someone.

291
00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:20.970
Well. you're just gonna
have to explain to your date

292
00:17:21.053 --> 00:17:23.055
the vicissitudes of tribal police work

293
00:17:23.138 --> 00:17:26.725
don't always jibe with having a social life.

294
00:17:26.809 --> 00:17:29.645
What does he mean. vicissitudes?

295
00:17:29.728 --> 00:17:31.564
I would reschedule.

296
00:17:31.647 --> 00:17:34.859
All right. from the "Time Flies" file.

297
00:17:34.942 --> 00:17:37.444
the Wash-O-Mat reported
someone stole the wall clock.

298
00:17:37.528 --> 00:17:39.154
Bigman. want that one?

299
00:17:39.238 --> 00:17:41.448
I'll make sure I'll dust for prints.

300
00:17:41.532 --> 00:17:45.119
Wapi Johnson says UFOs have
been visiting his pasture.

301
00:17:45.202 --> 00:17:47.121
- stealing his sheep again.
- [snickering]

302
00:17:47.204 --> 00:17:49.415
Might need one of you to. uh.
camp out over there

303
00:17:49.498 --> 00:17:52.918
for a few nights.
see what's really going on.

304
00:17:53.002 --> 00:17:54.461
Okay.

305
00:17:54.545 --> 00:17:56.463
Well. it looks like a 16-year-old girl.

306
00:17:56.547 --> 00:17:57.882
Billie Tsosie. just ran away

307
00:17:57.965 --> 00:17:59.091
from St. Catherine's three days ago.

308
00:17:59.174 --> 00:18:00.676
Yeah. All right.

309
00:18:00.759 --> 00:18:02.219
Whoo.
[clapping]

310
00:18:02.303 --> 00:18:04.263
All right. settle down.

311
00:18:04.346 --> 00:18:06.056
We need to make sure she's safe.

312
00:18:06.140 --> 00:18:07.975
So let's keep a lookout.

313
00:18:08.058 --> 00:18:13.439
5'7". slight build. last seen
wearing her school uniform.

314
00:18:13.522 --> 00:18:14.940
Let's put out some feelers. all right?

315
00:18:15.024 --> 00:18:16.775
That's it.

316
00:18:16.859 --> 00:18:20.362
[in Diné]
Be careful. be mindful.

317
00:18:20.446 --> 00:18:22.197
[both speaking Diné]

318
00:18:22.281 --> 00:18:24.742
[phone ringing]

319
00:18:26.327 --> 00:18:28.996
[in English] Request forms
for when we need time off?

320
00:18:29.079 --> 00:18:31.290
The times. they are a-changin'. Natalie.

321
00:18:31.373 --> 00:18:32.291
Hmm.

322
00:18:34.960 --> 00:18:37.463
Didn't expect to see
you back for a few days.

323
00:18:37.546 --> 00:18:39.006
Any luck?

324
00:18:39.089 --> 00:18:42.009
A few rabbits. deer.

325
00:18:42.092 --> 00:18:43.552
Where were you exactly?

326
00:18:43.636 --> 00:18:46.180
[chuckles] That's a nice try.

327
00:18:46.263 --> 00:18:49.475
I tell you. half the rez
will be hunting my spot.

328
00:18:49.558 --> 00:18:51.268
I'm gonna go head out to St. Catherine.

329
00:18:51.352 --> 00:18:52.853
see about that runner.

330
00:18:52.937 --> 00:18:55.356
Yeah. I'll go with you.

331
00:18:55.439 --> 00:18:57.274
[phone ringing]

332
00:18:59.234 --> 00:19:01.820
How'd it go out there?

333
00:19:01.904 --> 00:19:04.823
I'm not talking about the hunting.

334
00:19:04.907 --> 00:19:07.076
Long periods of nothing

335
00:19:07.159 --> 00:19:10.537
punctuated by moments of nothing.

336
00:19:10.621 --> 00:19:15.918
So does it help.
long periods of nothing?

337
00:19:16.001 --> 00:19:18.837
I don't know.

338
00:19:18.921 --> 00:19:22.049
Something weird did happen. though.

339
00:19:22.132 --> 00:19:23.717
Oh. yeah?

340
00:19:23.801 --> 00:19:27.262
I was tracking a buck.
real mature. broad neck.

341
00:19:27.346 --> 00:19:29.807
rack the size
of a goddamn chandelier.

342
00:19:29.890 --> 00:19:32.309
So I had it in my scope.

343
00:19:32.393 --> 00:19:34.937
Right when I was
about to pull the trigger.

344
00:19:35.020 --> 00:19:37.189
it just turns and stares at me.

345
00:19:37.272 --> 00:19:39.942
like it understood why I was there.

346
00:19:40.025 --> 00:19:41.485
like it was his time.

347
00:19:43.529 --> 00:19:48.242
Telling you. Joe. no matter
who you are. where you stand…

348
00:19:48.325 --> 00:19:51.704
[playful music]

349
00:19:51.787 --> 00:19:58.585
<i>♪♪</i>

350
00:19:58.669 --> 00:20:00.129
Well. those are words to live by.

351
00:20:00.212 --> 00:20:02.464
That's what I do.

352
00:20:02.548 --> 00:20:04.633
[school bell rings]

353
00:20:04.717 --> 00:20:07.469
Second time this month
she's up and run.

354
00:20:07.553 --> 00:20:12.683
Her grandda usually returns her
to us. but she's a wild one.

355
00:20:12.766 --> 00:20:15.185
And three days gone
with no word from him

356
00:20:15.269 --> 00:20:16.729
tells me this time is different.

357
00:20:16.812 --> 00:20:18.230
And where does her grandpa live?

358
00:20:18.313 --> 00:20:20.691
Way up north of Sheep Springs.

359
00:20:20.774 --> 00:20:21.984
Well. if she's on foot.

360
00:20:22.067 --> 00:20:23.861
she'll never make it in this heat.

361
00:20:23.944 --> 00:20:26.196
Exactly why I called you.

362
00:20:32.619 --> 00:20:34.538
That's her with her grandda.

363
00:20:38.792 --> 00:20:41.670
[footsteps approaching]

364
00:20:44.381 --> 00:20:48.761
[sighs] Girls. this is
Lieutenant Leaphorn

365
00:20:48.844 --> 00:20:52.139
and Sergeant Chee
of the Navajo Tribal Police.

366
00:20:52.222 --> 00:20:54.141
I told them that if anyone
knows where Billie is.

367
00:20:54.224 --> 00:20:55.601
it's one of you.

368
00:20:55.684 --> 00:20:57.144
Good morning.

369
00:20:57.227 --> 00:20:58.937
[all] Good morning.

370
00:20:59.021 --> 00:21:01.440
You won't be doing Billie
any favors by not telling

371
00:21:01.523 --> 00:21:03.942
these officers what you know.

372
00:21:04.026 --> 00:21:07.071
We all want her back
and safe. don't we?

373
00:21:13.327 --> 00:21:16.497
Sister. can we have
a few minutes alone with them?

374
00:21:16.580 --> 00:21:18.916
Do you think that's wise. Lieutenant?

375
00:21:18.999 --> 00:21:20.793
I think it might be. yes.

376
00:21:27.007 --> 00:21:30.010
Billie lives with her grandpa
up north of Sheep Springs.

377
00:21:30.094 --> 00:21:33.722
Well. that's a good four or
five days from here on foot.

378
00:21:33.806 --> 00:21:36.642
Longer if she stays off the main roads.

379
00:21:36.725 --> 00:21:40.229
And if she's not on the main
roads. she's in the desert.

380
00:21:40.312 --> 00:21:42.981
It's easy to get lost out there. hurt.

381
00:21:43.065 --> 00:21:45.275
She's not lost.

382
00:21:45.359 --> 00:21:48.237
[suspenseful music]

383
00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:49.780
<i>♪♪</i>

384
00:21:49.863 --> 00:21:52.324
Does she have any other
family here on the rez

385
00:21:52.407 --> 00:21:54.118
besides her grandpa?

386
00:21:54.201 --> 00:21:56.328
Is she close to anybody in her clans?

387
00:21:58.914 --> 00:22:00.666
You know if she has a boyfriend?

388
00:22:05.379 --> 00:22:08.590
Your friend could die out there.

389
00:22:08.674 --> 00:22:10.384
We don't know where she is.

390
00:22:10.467 --> 00:22:13.053
You don't know or won't tell?

391
00:22:13.137 --> 00:22:20.060
<i>♪♪</i>

392
00:22:22.938 --> 00:22:24.439
[clears throat]

393
00:22:28.443 --> 00:22:30.153
You have phone privileges here. right?

394
00:22:30.237 --> 00:22:31.530
Hmm?

395
00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:40.539
You think of something. just call me.

396
00:22:40.622 --> 00:22:42.666
Nobody will know you did. okay?

397
00:22:45.502 --> 00:22:46.962
[speaking Diné]

398
00:22:47.045 --> 00:22:51.425
<i>♪♪</i>

399
00:22:51.508 --> 00:22:54.928
[wind chimes tinkling]

400
00:22:55.012 --> 00:22:56.555
<i>They never get easier. do they?</i>

401
00:22:56.638 --> 00:22:58.765
- Who?
- Girls. women.

402
00:22:58.849 --> 00:23:00.475
[car door slams]

403
00:23:00.559 --> 00:23:03.312
You talk to them. they talk to you.

404
00:23:03.395 --> 00:23:06.690
But they never tell you
what they're really thinking.

405
00:23:06.773 --> 00:23:09.651
We're just meant to go through
life perennially in the dark?

406
00:23:09.735 --> 00:23:12.404
Yeah. you gotta learn
to read between the lines.

407
00:23:12.487 --> 00:23:14.531
Oh. yeah? How long does that take?

408
00:23:14.615 --> 00:23:16.283
I'll let you know when I get there.

409
00:23:16.366 --> 00:23:18.827
Currently on chapter 3
of "My Wife Left Me

410
00:23:18.911 --> 00:23:20.913
and I Still Don't Understand Why."

411
00:23:24.458 --> 00:23:26.668
[sighs]

412
00:23:26.752 --> 00:23:28.128
<i>♪ I'm in love ♪</i>

413
00:23:28.211 --> 00:23:29.922
I recall.

414
00:23:30.005 --> 00:23:32.466
She bought a pack of gum
and a tourist map.

415
00:23:32.549 --> 00:23:34.301
Tourist map.

416
00:23:34.384 --> 00:23:36.178
Maybe it was for the guy.

417
00:23:38.430 --> 00:23:39.973
What guy?

418
00:23:40.057 --> 00:23:41.266
A Indian guy.

419
00:23:41.350 --> 00:23:42.684
Early 20's maybe?

420
00:23:42.768 --> 00:23:45.896
- Navajo?
- Maybe. Think so.

421
00:23:45.979 --> 00:23:48.106
Real slick. the way he was dressed.

422
00:23:48.190 --> 00:23:49.775
Not from around here.

423
00:23:49.858 --> 00:23:51.860
Are you sure
he's not from around here?

424
00:23:51.944 --> 00:23:53.862
Car had California plates.

425
00:23:53.946 --> 00:23:55.197
Maybe he's from California.

426
00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:56.531
What kind of car?

427
00:23:56.615 --> 00:23:59.076
Red. two tone kind of thing.

428
00:23:59.159 --> 00:24:01.078
Probably back in California by now.

429
00:24:01.161 --> 00:24:02.663
But if you're going to California.

430
00:24:02.746 --> 00:24:04.915
why do you need a map
of the Navajo Nation?

431
00:24:04.998 --> 00:24:07.042
Ah.

432
00:24:07.125 --> 00:24:09.294
That's why you guys wear the
badge. I guess. huh? [chuckles]

433
00:24:09.378 --> 00:24:10.921
This guy. did it
seem like she knew him

434
00:24:11.004 --> 00:24:12.339
or like she was hitching a ride?

435
00:24:12.422 --> 00:24:13.966
No. they knew each other for sure.

436
00:24:14.049 --> 00:24:15.342
Bit of a reunion?

437
00:24:15.425 --> 00:24:16.843
Not a very happy one either.

438
00:24:16.927 --> 00:24:18.470
They were fighting.

439
00:24:18.553 --> 00:24:21.139
Didn't like that one bit. or him.

440
00:24:21.223 --> 00:24:23.350
[tense music]

441
00:24:23.433 --> 00:24:25.644
All right. Thanks. Roger.

442
00:24:25.727 --> 00:24:28.230
If you think of anything else.
give us a call.

443
00:24:28.313 --> 00:24:31.566
See him again. keep him here.

444
00:24:31.650 --> 00:24:33.318
Will do.

445
00:24:36.989 --> 00:24:38.699
[speaking Diné] Hello.

446
00:24:38.782 --> 00:24:40.575
Looking for anything in particular?

447
00:24:40.659 --> 00:24:42.077
All my jewelry is half off today.

448
00:24:42.160 --> 00:24:44.913
[door bell jingling]

449
00:24:46.206 --> 00:24:48.125
Probably make you a deal on
that rug. if you're interested.

450
00:24:48.208 --> 00:24:50.085
Let me know.

451
00:24:50.168 --> 00:24:55.882
<i>♪♪</i>

452
00:24:55.966 --> 00:24:58.343
[birds cawing]

453
00:24:58.427 --> 00:25:01.555
When we get back.
put an APB out on the car.

454
00:25:01.638 --> 00:25:04.433
Tomorrow morning.
we'll drive out to Ashie Begay's.

455
00:25:04.516 --> 00:25:06.101
see if he knows anything about this

456
00:25:06.184 --> 00:25:07.519
slick dressed guy from California.

457
00:25:07.602 --> 00:25:10.731
Copy that.

458
00:25:10.814 --> 00:25:13.734
[ominous music]

459
00:25:13.817 --> 00:25:20.741
<i>♪♪</i>

460
00:25:24.786 --> 00:25:27.706
[soft music]

461
00:25:27.789 --> 00:25:34.713
<i>♪♪</i>

462
00:25:52.606 --> 00:25:54.024
Where's Henry?

463
00:25:54.107 --> 00:25:55.609
Flagstaff.

464
00:25:55.692 --> 00:25:58.779
To pick up a fixture
for the front door.

465
00:25:58.862 --> 00:26:01.323
Finally getting around
to fixing that. huh?

466
00:26:01.406 --> 00:26:05.202
[distant dogs barking]

467
00:26:05.285 --> 00:26:08.497
I was hoping he'd be here.

468
00:26:08.580 --> 00:26:10.290
I wanted him to hear this too.

469
00:26:14.336 --> 00:26:15.837
I'm retiring. Mom.

470
00:26:17.839 --> 00:26:19.841
What brought you to this decision?

471
00:26:19.925 --> 00:26:22.636
I've been thinking about it for a while.

472
00:26:22.719 --> 00:26:25.097
Spending time in the mountains.

473
00:26:25.180 --> 00:26:28.016
not just hunting but sweating.

474
00:26:28.100 --> 00:26:29.893
trying to figure some things out.

475
00:26:29.976 --> 00:26:32.854
[distant dogs barking]

476
00:26:40.695 --> 00:26:42.405
You remember the deer meat
Emma's family

477
00:26:42.489 --> 00:26:43.949
prepared for our wedding?

478
00:26:44.032 --> 00:26:45.700
[speaking Diné]

479
00:26:45.784 --> 00:26:50.080
How neatly they wrapped it.
how beautiful Emma looked

480
00:26:50.163 --> 00:26:52.833
- in her rug dress that day…
- Mm-hmm.

481
00:26:52.916 --> 00:26:56.169
Carrying the ceremonial
basket with the mush.

482
00:26:56.253 --> 00:27:00.590
And I remember thinking
she would be good for you.

483
00:27:00.674 --> 00:27:03.093
She was.

484
00:27:03.176 --> 00:27:05.554
When your father and I got married.

485
00:27:05.637 --> 00:27:08.932
I thought I could change him
back to the man I knew.

486
00:27:09.015 --> 00:27:11.143
before he went to the war.

487
00:27:14.229 --> 00:27:17.315
It took me a long time to figure out

488
00:27:17.399 --> 00:27:22.821
he wasn't going to change
just because I wanted him to.

489
00:27:22.904 --> 00:27:24.781
I don't know how
you stayed with him.

490
00:27:24.865 --> 00:27:28.451
In those days.
that's what people did.

491
00:27:28.535 --> 00:27:30.829
But even if they didn't.

492
00:27:30.912 --> 00:27:33.748
I would have stayed for you…
[speaking Diné]

493
00:27:39.171 --> 00:27:42.465
Well. maybe that's
one of the reasons Emma left.

494
00:27:42.549 --> 00:27:45.135
'cause she realized
she couldn't change me.

495
00:27:45.218 --> 00:27:49.139
She no longer had JJ
to tie her to me. so.

496
00:27:50.765 --> 00:27:53.643
[in Diné] The elders taught us.

497
00:27:54.394 --> 00:27:57.147
time in the mountains can give us

498
00:27:57.814 --> 00:28:01.818
a clear purpose in life.

499
00:28:01.902 --> 00:28:08.909
If you do this for yourself
and not for Emma or anyone else.

500
00:28:09.951 --> 00:28:13.997
my son. she will see you.

501
00:28:15.332 --> 00:28:17.584
[in Diné] I Want to believe that.

502
00:28:20.712 --> 00:28:23.089
[in Diné] Stay for supper.

503
00:28:23.924 --> 00:28:26.635
It's not often we have this time.
just you and me.

504
00:28:26.760 --> 00:28:27.677
[in Diné] Yes

505
00:28:28.803 --> 00:28:35.727
<i>♪♪</i>

506
00:28:48.031 --> 00:28:50.784
[in English] <i>What were</i>
<i>you doing at St. Catherine's?</i>

507
00:28:50.867 --> 00:28:54.162
We got a runner who
lives up with her grandpa

508
00:28:54.246 --> 00:28:55.997
up near Sheep Springs.

509
00:28:56.081 --> 00:28:58.792
I'm gonna head out there tomorrow.

510
00:28:58.875 --> 00:29:02.546
Roger saw her with this dude.
California plates.

511
00:29:02.629 --> 00:29:03.964
had a bad feeling about him.

512
00:29:08.385 --> 00:29:10.178
Oh. I see that look.

513
00:29:10.262 --> 00:29:12.222
You wish you'd been there.

514
00:29:20.605 --> 00:29:22.232
Aren't you worried
about how this would work?

515
00:29:25.068 --> 00:29:27.821
If I came back?

516
00:29:27.904 --> 00:29:28.863
No.

517
00:29:38.415 --> 00:29:41.418
I'm not a mind reader. Bern.

518
00:29:41.501 --> 00:29:43.878
Are we even
in the same relationship?

519
00:29:43.962 --> 00:29:45.255
Okay. okay.

520
00:29:45.338 --> 00:29:46.548
Tell me what I should
be worried about.

521
00:29:46.631 --> 00:29:48.008
and I'll be worried.

522
00:29:48.091 --> 00:29:50.677
[pensive music]

523
00:29:50.760 --> 00:29:53.555
[sighs]

524
00:29:56.516 --> 00:29:59.227
What if we're working
on the same case.

525
00:29:59.311 --> 00:30:01.730
and we have a disagreement?

526
00:30:01.813 --> 00:30:04.274
I don't wanna be
in competition with you.

527
00:30:04.357 --> 00:30:06.443
Simple. We take it to Joe.

528
00:30:10.822 --> 00:30:12.365
What if I make a mistake?

529
00:30:12.449 --> 00:30:14.075
What if I do?

530
00:30:16.077 --> 00:30:18.496
What if I make a mistake
that gets you hurt?

531
00:30:18.580 --> 00:30:23.877
<i>♪♪</i>

532
00:30:23.960 --> 00:30:26.671
Hey.

533
00:30:26.755 --> 00:30:28.673
[sighs]

534
00:30:28.757 --> 00:30:34.929
<i>♪♪</i>

535
00:30:35.013 --> 00:30:37.849
I don't wanna mess this up.

536
00:30:37.932 --> 00:30:40.435
Bern.

537
00:30:40.518 --> 00:30:44.022
You're not gonna mess anything up.

538
00:30:44.105 --> 00:30:47.150
And I'm sorry for what
you went through down there.

539
00:30:47.233 --> 00:30:49.569
I know it's rattled you.

540
00:30:49.653 --> 00:30:51.988
but that isn't gonna happen here.

541
00:30:52.072 --> 00:30:54.115
Nobody's got any secrets around here.

542
00:30:54.199 --> 00:30:55.950
Nobody's gonna betray you.

543
00:30:56.034 --> 00:30:59.037
And I'm here.

544
00:31:02.916 --> 00:31:05.418
Okay.

545
00:31:05.502 --> 00:31:07.379
And I've got you.

546
00:31:07.462 --> 00:31:14.386
<i>♪♪</i>

547
00:31:15.553 --> 00:31:18.390
[Sharon Burch's "Sacred Wind"]

548
00:31:18.473 --> 00:31:24.771
<i>♪♪</i>

549
00:31:24.854 --> 00:31:27.774
[horses whinnying]

550
00:31:27.857 --> 00:31:34.823
<i>♪♪</i>

551
00:31:34.906 --> 00:31:36.282
[birds cawing]

552
00:31:36.366 --> 00:31:39.244
[singing in Diné]

553
00:31:39.327 --> 00:31:46.209
<i>♪♪</i>

554
00:32:21.953 --> 00:32:24.038
Mr. Begay. [speaking Diné]

555
00:32:24.122 --> 00:32:25.874
[speaking Diné]

556
00:32:25.957 --> 00:32:27.333
I'm Lieutenant Leaphorn.

557
00:32:27.417 --> 00:32:29.419
This is Sergeant Chee.

558
00:32:29.502 --> 00:32:31.087
I know who you are.

559
00:32:31.171 --> 00:32:32.589
Well. we wanted to ask
you a few questions

560
00:32:32.672 --> 00:32:34.758
about your granddaughter. Billie.

561
00:32:34.841 --> 00:32:36.801
Well. she ran away from school.

562
00:32:36.885 --> 00:32:38.178
Wondering if she
was here or been here

563
00:32:38.261 --> 00:32:39.387
in the last three days?

564
00:32:39.471 --> 00:32:41.222
She's been gone three days.

565
00:32:41.306 --> 00:32:43.349
and you're just coming here now?

566
00:32:43.433 --> 00:32:46.144
I'll find her myself.

567
00:32:46.227 --> 00:32:48.813
Did your granddaughter
have a boyfriend. Mr. Begay?

568
00:32:48.897 --> 00:32:50.398
I don't know.

569
00:32:50.482 --> 00:32:54.444
Drives a red two-tone sedan.
California plates.

570
00:32:54.527 --> 00:32:57.363
She was seen at the Trading
Post with a young Navajo guy.

571
00:32:57.447 --> 00:33:01.117
described as a slick dresser.
not from around here.

572
00:33:01.201 --> 00:33:03.870
They drove off together in that car.

573
00:33:03.953 --> 00:33:05.330
You know him?

574
00:33:05.413 --> 00:33:07.165
[sighs]

575
00:33:07.248 --> 00:33:11.127
It might be her cousin. Albert Gorman.

576
00:33:11.211 --> 00:33:12.754
[suspenseful music]

577
00:33:12.837 --> 00:33:13.880
And who's he?

578
00:33:13.963 --> 00:33:15.673
Criminal.

579
00:33:15.757 --> 00:33:17.509
My daughter's boy.

580
00:33:17.592 --> 00:33:21.721
Took him and his brother
to Los Angeles a long time ago.

581
00:33:21.805 --> 00:33:23.598
He forgot where he came from.

582
00:33:23.681 --> 00:33:25.225
What about Billie's parents?

583
00:33:25.308 --> 00:33:27.477
She doesn't have any.

584
00:33:27.560 --> 00:33:30.063
Thanks for letting me know.

585
00:33:30.146 --> 00:33:31.064
I'll find her myself.

586
00:33:31.147 --> 00:33:32.774
Hold-- hold-- hold on.

587
00:33:35.276 --> 00:33:37.904
Did you know Albert Gorman
was back on the rez?

588
00:33:37.987 --> 00:33:39.614
No.

589
00:33:39.697 --> 00:33:41.908
Can you think of any reason
he'd be here.

590
00:33:41.991 --> 00:33:44.327
why she'd leave school to be with him?

591
00:33:44.410 --> 00:33:46.704
None good.

592
00:33:46.788 --> 00:33:49.290
All I know is. if she's
with Albert. she's in trouble.

593
00:33:49.374 --> 00:33:53.920
<i>♪♪</i>

594
00:33:54.003 --> 00:33:55.672
[speaking Diné]

595
00:33:55.755 --> 00:33:58.633
[camera shutter clicking]

596
00:33:58.716 --> 00:34:05.640
<i>♪♪</i>

597
00:34:18.570 --> 00:34:21.489
[pensive music]

598
00:34:21.573 --> 00:34:28.496
<i>♪♪</i>

599
00:34:43.303 --> 00:34:46.222
[fire crackling]

600
00:34:52.562 --> 00:34:55.857
[breathes deeply]

601
00:35:09.203 --> 00:35:10.997
[sighs]

602
00:35:21.049 --> 00:35:21.966
[sighs]

603
00:35:24.886 --> 00:35:27.513
[phone ringing]

604
00:35:29.515 --> 00:35:33.144
[cheers and applause]

605
00:35:33.227 --> 00:35:34.520
Whoo. Bern!

606
00:35:34.604 --> 00:35:36.981
[shouting. whooping]

607
00:35:37.065 --> 00:35:39.359
Okay!

608
00:35:39.442 --> 00:35:42.236
Well. well.

609
00:35:42.320 --> 00:35:45.740
Look what the cat dragged in.

610
00:35:45.823 --> 00:35:48.493
It's nice to have you back. Sergeant.

611
00:35:48.576 --> 00:35:50.828
It's good to see you. too. Chee.

612
00:35:53.122 --> 00:35:54.207
You buying this?

613
00:35:54.290 --> 00:35:56.334
Not even a little bit.

614
00:35:56.417 --> 00:35:57.919
Oh!

615
00:35:58.002 --> 00:35:59.879
Almost as if I never left.

616
00:35:59.963 --> 00:36:02.382
Get settled and we'll bring
you up to speed when we're at--

617
00:36:02.465 --> 00:36:04.759
Hey. you find that
St. Catherine's runner yet?

618
00:36:04.842 --> 00:36:07.011
[phone ringing]

619
00:36:07.095 --> 00:36:08.179
Well. somebody's got loose lips.

620
00:36:10.181 --> 00:36:11.933
Not yet. no.

621
00:36:12.016 --> 00:36:13.267
Well. I'd like to go out there.

622
00:36:13.351 --> 00:36:17.063
We've already been out there. so.

623
00:36:17.146 --> 00:36:21.526
Well. I know you have.
but I haven't.

624
00:36:21.609 --> 00:36:23.152
With all due respect. Lieutenant.

625
00:36:23.236 --> 00:36:25.029
You hearing this. Joe?

626
00:36:25.113 --> 00:36:27.073
Not back 60 seconds.
and she's already chalked up

627
00:36:27.156 --> 00:36:28.241
- her first "all due respect."
- Mm.

628
00:36:28.324 --> 00:36:29.617
- Oh. thank you.
- Impressive.

629
00:36:29.701 --> 00:36:31.244
- Joe?
- [speaking Diné]

630
00:36:31.327 --> 00:36:34.080
Forgot what a pleasure it is
to work with you two.

631
00:36:34.163 --> 00:36:35.581
Go.

632
00:36:35.665 --> 00:36:39.252
Maybe you'll have
better luck than we did.

633
00:36:39.335 --> 00:36:42.130
[pensive music]

634
00:36:42.213 --> 00:36:49.137
<i>♪♪</i>

635
00:36:54.100 --> 00:36:56.436
Hannah. come with me.

636
00:36:56.519 --> 00:36:59.856
The policewoman wants
to talk with Jane.

637
00:37:03.693 --> 00:37:05.319
I'm glad to see
you've made something

638
00:37:05.403 --> 00:37:07.405
of yourself. Bernadette.

639
00:37:07.488 --> 00:37:09.949
It's very nice of you
to notice. Sister.

640
00:37:10.033 --> 00:37:11.409
Hmm.

641
00:37:18.166 --> 00:37:19.292
Hey.

642
00:37:29.552 --> 00:37:31.471
You gotta wipe those first.

643
00:37:33.890 --> 00:37:35.808
I know you're just here
because of Billie.

644
00:37:35.892 --> 00:37:38.436
Do you know where she is?

645
00:37:38.519 --> 00:37:41.272
It's weird how people
only care once we disappear.

646
00:37:43.524 --> 00:37:45.151
Well. guess what?

647
00:37:45.234 --> 00:37:49.322
When I used to disappear
from here. nobody cared.

648
00:37:49.405 --> 00:37:51.324
Oh. and I'm supposed
to feel sorry for you?

649
00:37:51.407 --> 00:37:53.826
Well. you don't have to
feel sorry for me. Jane.

650
00:37:53.910 --> 00:37:56.079
You heard what Sister Regina said.

651
00:37:56.162 --> 00:37:59.373
I made something of myself.

652
00:38:06.839 --> 00:38:12.720
You know. I used to think
it was so cruel.

653
00:38:12.804 --> 00:38:15.556
We'd be up there starving.

654
00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:17.850
All this food down here.
we weren't allowed to eat it.

655
00:38:17.934 --> 00:38:19.477
Well. that hasn't changed.

656
00:38:19.560 --> 00:38:24.982
<i>♪♪</i>

657
00:38:25.066 --> 00:38:27.652
You know. there were
nights I'd lie in bed.

658
00:38:27.735 --> 00:38:31.823
and I swear I could
hear frybread sizzling.

659
00:38:31.906 --> 00:38:34.700
I could smell it.

660
00:38:34.784 --> 00:38:37.120
First place I'd go
when I ran out of here

661
00:38:37.203 --> 00:38:38.913
was the Chat 'N Chew.

662
00:38:38.996 --> 00:38:42.083
Oh. their frybread tastes
just like my grandma's.

663
00:38:42.166 --> 00:38:45.419
just a greasy slab of mutton.

664
00:38:45.503 --> 00:38:47.338
Mmm. mmm. mmm.

665
00:38:50.091 --> 00:38:52.593
How about you?

666
00:38:52.677 --> 00:38:54.637
French fries.

667
00:38:54.720 --> 00:38:56.264
Ketchup?

668
00:38:56.347 --> 00:38:59.433
Extra salt. Oh. and they have to be hot.

669
00:38:59.517 --> 00:39:01.102
Fugitive fries.

670
00:39:01.185 --> 00:39:02.979
- Extra salt.
- Extra hot.

671
00:39:03.062 --> 00:39:04.897
Right.
[both chuckle]

672
00:39:09.318 --> 00:39:10.611
How about Billie?

673
00:39:13.322 --> 00:39:15.908
Where's she go when she gets out?

674
00:39:15.992 --> 00:39:20.037
Well. she--

675
00:39:20.121 --> 00:39:22.540
um…

676
00:39:22.623 --> 00:39:24.584
there's a diner.

677
00:39:24.667 --> 00:39:26.919
She likes the milkshakes there.

678
00:39:31.299 --> 00:39:34.844
[engine humming]

679
00:39:34.927 --> 00:39:37.221
<i>♪ Just as plain as day ♪</i>

680
00:39:37.305 --> 00:39:38.764
<i>♪ Ah. well. a-here comes trouble ♪</i>

681
00:39:38.848 --> 00:39:40.349
<i>♪ That I never thought I'd see ♪</i>

682
00:39:40.433 --> 00:39:42.727
You're telling me
Leroy just disappeared?

683
00:39:42.810 --> 00:39:44.187
I don't know what
you want me to do.

684
00:39:44.270 --> 00:39:45.605
[phone ringing]
The rez is big. Albert.

685
00:39:45.688 --> 00:39:47.565
I want you to help me find him.

686
00:39:47.648 --> 00:39:50.568
<i>♪ You talk about heartaches ♪</i>

687
00:39:50.651 --> 00:39:53.029
<i>♪ Where in the world ya been? ♪</i>

688
00:39:53.112 --> 00:39:54.572
<i>♪ I ain't had the miseries ♪</i>

689
00:39:54.655 --> 00:39:56.532
Hon?

690
00:39:56.616 --> 00:39:59.452
You have the prettiest ears of
any woman I ever set eyes on.

691
00:39:59.535 --> 00:40:02.038
Have I told you that?

692
00:40:02.121 --> 00:40:05.458
You've complimented every
part of me at some point. shug.

693
00:40:05.541 --> 00:40:08.044
Well. I'd love them ears a whole lot more

694
00:40:08.127 --> 00:40:10.421
if they heard that phone.

695
00:40:10.504 --> 00:40:12.757
Oh. [laughs]

696
00:40:12.840 --> 00:40:14.425
All right.

697
00:40:17.011 --> 00:40:18.304
Redhouse.

698
00:40:22.475 --> 00:40:24.602
Yeah. She's here.

699
00:40:24.685 --> 00:40:26.938
You wanna talk to her?

700
00:40:27.021 --> 00:40:29.315
[phone rings]

701
00:40:31.359 --> 00:40:33.444
Navajo Tribal Police.
This is Sergeant Chee.

702
00:40:33.527 --> 00:40:34.779
Redhouse Diner.

703
00:40:34.862 --> 00:40:36.280
Billie's there right now with Gorman.

704
00:40:36.364 --> 00:40:37.657
- Where are you?
<i>- St. Catherine's.</i>

705
00:40:37.740 --> 00:40:38.783
I'm on my way.

706
00:40:38.866 --> 00:40:40.993
Well. how you know it's them?

707
00:40:41.077 --> 00:40:41.994
Redhouse Diner.

708
00:40:42.078 --> 00:40:43.079
Billie and Gorman.

709
00:40:43.162 --> 00:40:44.830
Bern's headed there now.

710
00:40:44.914 --> 00:40:48.459
[tense music]

711
00:40:48.542 --> 00:40:51.420
[engines humming]

712
00:40:55.716 --> 00:40:57.885
[tires screech]

713
00:40:57.969 --> 00:40:59.887
[engines stop]

714
00:40:59.971 --> 00:41:03.015
[unsettling music]

715
00:41:03.099 --> 00:41:08.437
<i>♪♪</i>

716
00:41:08.521 --> 00:41:11.148
[distorted singing]

717
00:41:11.232 --> 00:41:15.236
<i>♪♪</i>

718
00:41:15.319 --> 00:41:18.155
[door creaking]

719
00:41:18.239 --> 00:41:19.824
Go around back.

720
00:41:25.454 --> 00:41:27.748
[distorted singing]

721
00:41:27.832 --> 00:41:34.755
<i>♪♪</i>

722
00:41:39.844 --> 00:41:40.928
Bernie. you see this?

723
00:41:43.097 --> 00:41:44.265
Yeah.

724
00:41:46.892 --> 00:41:50.187
[distorted singing]

725
00:41:50.271 --> 00:41:57.194
<i>♪♪</i>

726
00:41:57.278 --> 00:41:58.612
We got shells.

727
00:42:00.906 --> 00:42:02.616
Navajo Tribal Police!

728
00:42:04.577 --> 00:42:05.536
Go.

729
00:42:05.619 --> 00:42:12.543
<i>♪♪</i>

730
00:42:20.843 --> 00:42:22.845
[electricity buzzing]

731
00:43:28.411 --> 00:43:30.037
Welcome home.

732
00:43:36.544 --> 00:43:37.503
[sighs]

733
00:43:37.586 --> 00:43:43.759
<i>♪♪</i>

734
00:43:50.683 --> 00:43:53.644
[tense music]

735
00:43:53.727 --> 00:44:00.609
<i>♪♪</i>
